## Why This Is Asked
Understanding how to count inversions online with limited memory and batched updates tests both data structures and amortized reasoning.

## Key Concepts
- Fenwick tree for prefix sums; online per-element updates
- Inversion counting formula: add current_seen - count_of_≤v
- Amortized batch analysis and memory scaling with M

## Code Example
```javascript
class Fenwick {
  constructor(n){ this.f=[0]; for(let i=1;i<=n;i++) this.f[i]=0; }
  add(i,delta){ for(i+=1;i<this.f.length;i+=i&-i) this.f[i]+=delta }
  sum(i){ let s=0; for(i+=1;i>0;i-=i&-i) s+=this.f[i]; return s }
}
function processBatch(batch, M, fen, totalSeen){ let inversions=0; for(const v of batch){ inversions += totalSeen - fen.sum(v); fen.add(v,1); totalSeen++; } return {inversions, totalSeen}; }
```

