## Why This Is Asked
Tests an engineer's ability to design incremental statistics with tight per-batch updates and constant-time queries, a realistic analytics constraint.

## Key Concepts
- Maintaining a nonlinear statistic (entropy) via a linearizable surrogate S
- Precomputing k log k and handling zero edges cleanly
- Incremental updates using two counters per move

## Code Example
```javascript
// G[k] = k * Math.log(k), with G[0] = 0
function processBatch(batch, freq, G, S, n) {
  for (const {from,to} of batch) {
    const fFrom = freq[from];
    freq[from] = fFrom - 1;
    S.value += G[fFrom - 1] - G[fFrom];
    const fTo = freq[to];
    freq[to] = fTo + 1;
    S.value += G[fTo + 1] - G[fTo];
  }
  return Math.log(n) - S.value / n;
}
```

