## Why This Is Asked
Tests dynamic skyline maintenance with batch updates, including amortized analysis and practical data-structure design.

## Key Concepts
- **2D dominance and Pareto frontier**: A point p dominates q if p.x ≥ q.x and p.y ≥ q.y with at least one strict inequality.
- **Invariant**: Frontier F is sorted by x with strictly increasing y, ensuring no two frontier points dominate each other.
- **Amortized analysis**: Each point is inserted once and removed at most once over n total points.
- **Space**: Uses O(n) space for all historical points plus O(|F|) for the current frontier.

## Data Structure
Use a balanced binary search tree (e.g., TreeMap) keyed by x-coordinate, with y-values stored alongside. This enables O(log |F|) insertion, O(1) access to the rightmost (largest x) point, and O(|F|) in-order traversal.

## Algorithm
1. Sort incoming batch by x-coordinate (O(B log B)).
2. Merge with frontier: for each batch point p, if p.y > current max frontier y, insert p and prune any frontier points with y ≤ p.y.
3. Enumerate frontier via in-order traversal.

## Code Example
```javascript
class Skyline {
  constructor() { this.frontier = new Map(); }

  insertBatch(points) {
    const sorted = points.sort((a, b) => a.x - b.x);
    let maxY = 0;

    for (const p of sorted) {
      if (p.y <= maxY) continue;

      for (const [x, y] of this.frontier) {
        if (y <= p.y) this.frontier.delete(x);
      }

      this.frontier.set(p.x, p.y);
      maxY = p.y;
    }
  }

  getFrontier() {
    return Array.from(this.frontier.entries())
      .sort((a, b) => a[0] - b[0]);
  }
}
```

## Complexity Summary
| Operation | Cost |
|-----------|------|
| Batch insertion | O(B log B + |F|) amortized |
| Enumerate frontier | O(|F|) |
| Space | O(n) |

