## Key Concepts
- **Parity (Bipartiteness) DSU**: Maintains connected components with parity labels to detect odd cycles, enabling O(α(N)) union-find operations.
- **Rollback / Persistent State**: Allows reverting DSU state within a block to test multiple edge configurations efficiently.
- **Time-based Block Decomposition**: Divides updates into blocks, rebuilding the DSU at block boundaries while processing updates within blocks using rollback.
- **Trade-offs**: Balancing rebuild cost (at block boundaries) against per-update cost (within blocks).

## Impact of Batch Size B
- **Larger B**: More edges processed per batch → fewer rebuilds → lower amortized cost per edge, but higher memory overhead for rollback structures.
- **Smaller B**: More frequent rebuilds → higher amortized cost, but lower memory since fewer rollback checkpoints are needed.
- **Optimal B**: Typically Θ(√M) balances O(√M · α(N)) per batch with O(M) space.

## Code Example
```cpp
struct ParityDSU {
    vector<int> parent, rank, parity;
    struct Change { int u, oldParent, oldRank, oldParity; };
    vector<Change> stack;

    ParityDSU(int n) : parent(n), rank(n, 0), parity(n, 0) {
        iota(parent.begin(), parent.end(), 0);
    }

    int find(int x) {
        if (parent[x] == x) return x;
        return find(parent[x]);
    }

    int findWithParity(int x) {
        if (parent[x] == x) return x;
        int p = findWithParity(parent[x]);
        parity[x] ^= parity[parent[x]];
        return parent[x] = p;
    }

    bool unite(int x, int y) {
        x = findWithParity(x);
        y = findWithParity(y);
        if (x == y) return parity[x] != parity[y];
        if (rank[x] < rank[y]) swap(x, y);
        stack.push_back({y, parent[y], rank[y], parity[y]});
        parent[y] = x;
        if (rank[x] == rank[y]) rank[x]++;
        parity[y] = parity[x] ^ parity[y] ^ 1;
        return true;
    }

    void snapshot() { stack.clear(); }
    void rollback() {
        while (!stack.empty()) {
            auto c = stack.back(); stack.pop_back();
            parent[c.u] = c.oldParent;
            rank[c.u] = c.oldRank;
            parity[c.u] = c.oldParity;
        }
    }
};
```

