Why This Is Asked
Tests dynamic tree maintenance and amortized batch updates with range operations.

Key Concepts
- Euler tour for subtree ranges
- Fenwick/segment tree for range add, point query
- Depths under re-parenting and how a subtree shifts
- Amortized cost with batches vs full DFS

Code Example
```javascript
function reparent(u, w) {
  let du = baseDepth[u] + bit.query(in[u]);
  let dw = baseDepth[w] + bit.query(in[w]);
  let delta = dw + 1 - du;
  if (delta !== 0) {
    bit.add(in[u], out[u], delta);
    globalSum += delta * size[u];
  }
}
